  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Imperial Hotel Tramontano enjoys one of the best locations in <a data-udi="umb://document/1b38a4293ff04cc8b2dd360a57a538d8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1b38a4293ff04cc8b2dd360a57a538d8}" title="Sorrento">Sorrento</a>. Set in the centre of the town, just a five-minute walk from Piazza Tasso, this cliff side property enjoys uninterrupted views over the Gulf of Naples.</p>
<p>Despite its central location, the hotel manages to create a peaceful atmosphere. Established gardens surround the building and this is where you’ll find the lovely freshwater pool with plenty of sun loungers and umbrellas. There’s also a snack bar nearby for refreshing drinks and light lunches, making it easy to enjoy a relaxed day. You’ll also find direct access to the Mediterranean Sea below via a lift in the hotel which is open from 01 Jun - 30 Oct.<br />The interiors of the hotel reflect its history, with traditional furnishings throughout and a classic style.</p>
<p>Originally a 19th century private villa, the Imperial Hotel Tramontano has played host to some illustrious guests since it became a hotel, including Lord Byron, Milton, Keats and even King Edward VII. Several spacious lounges in the hotel provide a welcoming spot to relax with a drink, and the panoramic vistas you get from the sea view terraces can be hard to take yourself away from. In the evenings, traditional cuisine can be enjoyed in the elegant dining room, where large windows overlooking the Bay ensure that you can admire the sunset over a romantic meal.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 5 mins by private car from Naples Airport.</p>]]></description>
